  %section#testimonials.stripe
    .content
      %header
        %h1 Testimonials
      %section.entry-content
        %blockquote
          %p
            Having been part of leading Ruby on Windows workshops in the past,
            where half a day install-fest may have been the norm, RailsInstaller has made this so much easier.
            Both the Ruby Installer and RailsInstaller are great steps for the Ruby community toward
            welcoming Windows users to Ruby and Rails, instead of ignoring Windows
            as a 3rd-class citizen. What was once a many step process for
            installing Ruby, Rails, DevKit, Git, database support, etc. has now
            been consolidated into one easy-to-use RailsInstaller! Thanks for
            all the hours spent by those who created this installer for Windows.
          %footer
            \&mdash; Charley Baker,
            %a{:href => "http://groupon.com", :title => "The Daily Groupon | Coupons, Discounts, and Deals on the Best in Los Angeles"} Groupon.com
            \&amp;
            Gayle Craig
        %blockquote
          %p
            I teach Ruby/Rails to new developers every week and setting up systems
            can be EXTREMELY frustrating. Windows is now the easiest platform to
            setup thanks to RailsInstaller &mdash; one download, one install, and go!
          %footer
            \&mdash;
            %a{:href => "http://jumpstartlab.com", :title => "The Best Ruby on Rails Training - Jumpstart Lab"} Jeff Casimir
        %blockquote
          %p
            I'm giving some rails talk at college and RailsInstaller has
            saved my life! I can't imagine teaching Rails on Windows without it!
            Installing things on the university computers is a hard task.
            I was really worried about installing Rails until I found you guys!
            I love the fact that git is already installed!
          %footer
            \&mdash; Nicol&aacute;s Hock
        %blockquote
          %p
            No single tool or tactic has made my students&rsquo; learning curve gentler than RailsInstaller.
          %footer
            \&mdash;
            = succeed "," do
              %a{:href => "http://twitter.com/Cropcho", :title => "James Cropcho (Cropcho) on Twitter"} James Cropcho
            instructor of
            %a{:href => "http://generalassemb.ly/education/", :title => "Technology, Design, and Entrepreneurship Education at General Assembly"} classes and intensive workshops
            on first-time Rails development at
            %a{:href => "http://generalassemb.ly", :title => "Home"} General Assembly
